This paper focuses on deep learning-based sequential recommender systems, which are primarily used in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG) applications. The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence (AI) in these systems and the need to distinguish between different types of user behavior, which falls under the category of social and information networks (SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques in these systems, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.SI, and cs.CL.
